    # ========== PATH A — FULL YES ==========

label a4_s20_path_full_yes:

    t "Tonight I am not a medic."

    "She says it and the saying is a decision and the decision is visible in her face the way her face was visible when she capped the marker. It is the second capping of the night."

    a "Tessa."

    t "Say the yes back to me. I want the yes back."

    a "Yes. Tonight you are not a medic. Tonight you are the woman in the crew neck on the bench with the jacket beside her and I am the man in the room who is not bringing you his wounds."

    t "Thank you."

    tthought "I did not know I needed the yes said back. I know now. The saying back is the thing that makes the scene not mine alone."

    tthought "I have been alone inside my care-work for three years. Tonight the care-work is off the bench and I am off the bench with it and the bench has a jacket on it and nothing else."

    "He does not let go of her elbow."

    "His left hand moves from her shoulder to the side of her neck. Not the pulse point — the side. The place where neck meets jaw. Warm skin under warm hand. Her breath catches the way it catches when a person who has been holding a shape of attention finally gets to stop holding it."

    "She reaches up with her free hand and turns off the clip lamp on the board."

    "The board goes dark."

    "The vigil candle is still on."

    "The amber practical in the treatment corner is still on."

    "The light in the room is the light of a room that has agreed to be something other than a medical area for the length of the next hour."

    "She takes a step back — not to leave, to lead. Her hand does not leave his. She walks him the three steps to the bench. The jacket is on the bench. She does not move the jacket. The jacket is going to be on the bench for the whole scene. The jacket being on the bench is the scene's thesis object and removing it would undo the thesis."

    "She sits on the bench beside the jacket."

    "He sits on the other side of the jacket."

    "Then she reaches across the jacket and takes both his hands in hers."

    t "I am going to kiss you first."

    t "I am going to kiss you first because I want the first thing in this scene that is mine to be a thing I did, not a thing you did."

    a "Yes."

    "She does."

    "The kiss is not long. It is not short. It is the length of a kiss that has been inside a woman for seventeen days and has finally decided to come out. Her free hand is on the side of his face the way his hand was on the side of her neck. Her other hand is still holding his. The jacket is between them on the bench. Nothing moves it."

    "When she pulls back, her forehead rests against his."

    t "Okay."

    t "Okay."

    t "The hour starts now."

    # [INTIMATE CONTENT HERE]

    "The hour is an hour."

    jump a4_s20_aftercare

    # ========== PATH B — SLOW YES ==========

label a4_s20_path_slow_yes:

    t "Yes. But stay slow."

    t "I am still counting in my head. I cannot turn it off all the way. I did not know I was going to find out tonight that I cannot turn it off all the way — I thought I was going to find out I could. I am finding out I cannot. That is information and I am not going to lie about the information. I want the hour. I want it slower. I want it threaded around the count."

    a "Tell me how slow."

    "She almost laughs. It is not a laugh — it is the breath a laugh is made of, without the laugh on top of it."

    t "I do not know. I am going to know by feel. I need you to watch me for the speed."

    a "Okay. I am watching."

    tthought "He is going to be excellent at this. He is going to be excellent at this because he has spent the entire act being watched by me and he is going to know from the inside what it feels like to be the one being watched for speed. He is going to translate the watching into the other direction and I am going to be inside the translation."

    "He lifts his free hand and turns off the clip lamp on the board."

    "The board goes dark."

    "He does it for her because her one free hand is still holding his and she does not have a spare hand and he noticed she does not have a spare hand and he made the gesture the gesture of going-slow by doing her small chore for her before she had to ask."

    "She smiles. It is a small smile. The smile is not a smile of happiness. It is the smile of a woman noticing her scene is being run with care."

    t "You are already watching for the speed."

    a "I am."

    "She takes him to the bench the way Path A takes him to the bench — the jacket stays on the bench between them. She sits. He sits."

    "She does not kiss him first this time. She puts her hand on his chest and she breathes and she counts the breaths in her head because she cannot stop counting and she is trying to make the count be for something other than death tonight. The count is for her own breath. It is a slow count. She gets to four and the four feels like enough and she says enough to her own count and the count does not fully stop but it fades under the rest of what is happening in the scene."

    t "Kiss me when I nod."

    "She nods."

    "He kisses her. The kiss is slower than Path A's kiss because she asked for slower. It is the length of a kiss that is being checked against an internal counter that is still running at low volume. Her counter does not interrupt. Her counter is the thing the kiss is being paced against, not the thing interrupting it."

    t "Good."

    t "Slower than that by a little."

    a "Okay."

    # [INTIMATE CONTENT HERE]

    "The hour takes an hour and ten minutes because of the speed."

    jump a4_s20_aftercare

    # ========== PATH C — HELD ONLY ==========

label a4_s20_path_held_only:

    t "I cannot turn it off tonight."

    t "I thought I could. I walked over to the board tonight and I capped the marker and I told myself I could turn the counter off for an hour. I could not. It is still running. It is running louder than I have heard it run in four years."

    a "Tessa."

    t "Just hold me."

    t "That is the answer. The answer is not no to the hour. The answer is: the hour is going to be the shape of you holding me and me being held, and we are not going to cross the threshold tonight, because the threshold is not the wrong place and tonight is not the right night and I am allowed to know the difference."

    a "I am here."

    a "I am holding you."

    a "There is no part of tonight you have to do. There is not a part you skipped. Holding is the hour. Holding is the whole hour."

    "She nods into his collarbone."

    "Then her breath changes."

    "It does not break. It changes. There is a small intake she did not plan and a small catch on the exhale and she is not crying yet but she is standing at the edge of crying the way she stood at the edge of the dead column earlier tonight."

    "He does not tell her it is okay to cry. He does not narrate her permission to cry. Narrating it would be the wrong shape."

    "He does what she did for him in s05a — he turns off the clip lamp on the board with his free hand so her board can be in the dark for the next few minutes and so the only light in the room is the vigil candle and the one amber practical, which is to say the light is the light of a room that has permission to be a little smaller than usual."

    "The board goes dark."

    "She cries."

    tthought "Oh."

    tthought "I forgot what this is."

    tthought "I have not cried in four years. Not once. Not at Kesa. Not at Joren. Not at Liora. Not at the board moving a name the wrong direction at dusk. Not at any of it. I thought my crying was broken. I thought the ritual had absorbed the crying so that the crying did not need to happen anymore."

    tthought "The crying was not absorbed. The crying was waiting for a room where I did not have to count first."

    "She cries silently. Tessa does everything silently tonight. The crying is silent. The breath does not catch loudly. Her shoulders shake a small amount under his arm. Her cheek is wet against the place his collar meets his shoulder. His hand is in her hair and he is not saying anything because saying anything would be the wrong shape."

    "She cries for four minutes."

    "Then she stops."

    "She does not apologize for crying. Tessa does not apologize for a body doing a thing a body needed to do. She lifts her head and her face is wet and she looks at him and the look is a thank-you she does not have to say."

    t "Okay."

    t "The hour is still the hour. The hour is the holding. I am inside the hour."

    a "I know."

    "They sit that way for the rest of the hour."

    "She does not move to take the bench down to a lying-down position. She does not ask for the kiss. The intimacy tonight is the permission to cry for four minutes inside a room that was not going to ask her to count first, and the permission is more intimate than the threshold she did not cross."

    jump a4_s20_aftercare

    # ========== PHASE 9 — AFTERCARE ==========

label a4_s20_aftercare:

    # scene bg_medbay_main_aftercare_low with fade
    # play ambient "sfx/ambient/medbay_quiet_postcount.ogg" fadein 3.0

    "The hour is over."

    "It is the kind of over that does not announce itself. There is no clock in the room and she does not check the one on her datapad because the datapad is on the bench under the jacket. She knows the hour is over because the shape of the quiet has changed. She is a woman who knows the shapes of quiet."

    "She is sitting on the bench. Her hand is on the folded jacket beside her. She has not put the jacket back on."

    "He is sitting on the bench. His hand is on her hand which is on the jacket."

    "The clip lamp on the board is still off. The vigil candle is still on. The amber practical is still on. The light in the room has not changed."

    "She speaks first because she always does."

    t "The board is still there."

    a "I know."

    t "In the morning I will put the jacket back on and I will pick up the marker and if there is a new name I will write the new name and I will do the rule silently the way I have been doing the rule silently, and the count will run, and the count will run forever because the count is what I am."

    t "I am not choosing to stop counting."

    t "I am choosing to rest inside it."

    "She looks at him."

    t "Do you understand the difference."

    a "Yes."

    "He does. He understands the difference because he has spent half of Act IV watching her count and the other half of Act IV being counted by her, and tonight he has been shown the shape of the thing she needed in order to keep counting without the counting becoming the whole shape of her. The resting inside the count is not a vacation from the count. It is an instruction about how the count is going to be livable."

    athought "She is telling me the thing she told me in s12 about being held-not-fixed, but from the other side of the sentence."

    athought "S12 was me being held. Tonight was her being held. The sentence is one sentence. The sentence has two sides and we are doing both sides of it in the same act."

    athought "That is what the thesis of this act has been. Shared authority was always going to include shared being-held. The being-held is the thing the authority is protecting the space for."

    t "Aeron."

    a "Yes."

    t "You are not a wound I am fixing."

    a "I know."

    t "And I am not a medic you came to see."

    a "I know."

    t "Say it back."

    a "You are not a medic I came to see. You are Tessa. You are the woman in the crew neck on the bench. The jacket is beside you because the jacket is beside you tonight. In the morning the jacket will be on your shoulders again and in the morning you will count and in the morning I will be the one walking in and saying the eight-hundred brief is coming up in twenty minutes and you will tell Selene that Selene's commanders do not bleed on her floors. That is the morning. Tonight the jacket is on the bench."

    t "Yes."

    "She leans her head on his shoulder."

    "She is quiet for a long time."

    "Then:"

    t "Thank you for not bringing me your wounds tonight."

    a "Thank you for asking me not to."

    # scene bg_medbay_main_hold_wide with hold
    # play ambient "sfx/ambient/medbay_hold_low.ogg" fadein 4.0

    "The camera holds on the wide shot."

    "Both of them on the bench. The jacket between the two of them. The board behind them with its clip lamp off. The vigil candle still on. The amber practical still on. DAVEL OSTRA on the dead column is still the bottom entry. In a little while Tessa will put the jacket back on and they will walk out of the medbay and they will go to their separate next things and the act will keep doing what the act has been doing."

    "For now the two of them are on the bench."

    "The camera fades."

    # stop ambient fadeout 4.5
    # scene black with fade

